title: For Sale:  Spike's Tactical ST-T2 Heavy Buffer
postcontent:
Looking for a heavy buffer to replace your standard carbine buffer? Well, we came up with something that offers the HIGHEST performance at a reasonable price. The ST-T2 buffer is one of the softest shooting, smoothest, and quietest buffers on the market; not to mention it looks awesome! It doesn't have any weights to move around or fluids to leak out like some other buffers, so it's 100% maintenance free! 

Contact Armory Dynamics /REDACTED
www.armorydynamics.com
http://www.armorydynamics.com/parts/ar15-m16/lower-parts/spikes-tactical-st-t2-heavy-buffer.html

The ST-T2 buffer weighs in at 115g/4.05oz. (Depending on the density and size of the HDTP, the weight can vary slightly) and the body is CNC machined from solid billet Aluminum bar stock for strength and durability. To finish it all off, it's Anodized matte black and laser engraved with our Logo. 

So you're probably wondering what's inside of this thing to make this thing so great and different? 

Each ST-T2 buffer is filled with HDTP which is short for "High Density Tungsten Powder" and topped off with a Mil-Spec bumper. Because of this, there aren’t any reciprocating weights inside to make a lot of noise and it also makes for a very smooth cycling rifle. The ST-T2 eliminates the chance of bolt bounce, helps with muzzle rise when firing in full-auto, and cuts down on felt recoil. As you can tell, it's a HUGE upgrade from a Standard Carbine buffer! It's designed for .223/5.56 but it works in all Calibers! 

Get one for your AR-15 today and feel the difference!

title: For Sale:  32-40 Marlin Ballard Rifle (1 3/4 model) from late 1800s
postcontent:
Marlin Ballard rifle (MARLIN FIRE ARMS CO. NEW HAVEN CT, USA BALLARD'S PATENT, NOV 5 1861) from around 1889 or so.  

The rifle is in great shape given its age (see pictures).  It has a period accurate round barrel from GEO . C . SCHOYEN.

I had this rifle inspected by my gunsmith when I acquired it 6 or so years ago.  He test fired it and all was OK. 

The rifle has a set trigger, pop up rear elevation sight married with a hooded barrel band front sight (with crosshair).

The rifle comes with 40 rounds of 32-40 so that you can put the rifle back to the use for which it was intended instead of having it be a safe queen as it has for me.

Here is some other information about the Marlin Ballard:  23 distinct models and submodels of Ballard-design rifles were made by the Marlin factory. With so many follow-on variants, the Marlin Hunter became the Marlin No. 1 Hunter, then followed the No 1 1/2, Model 1 3/4, Model No. 2, and so on and so forth. These guns were designed for hard service and reliability with Rocky Mountain Sights, solid construction, and beefy stocks that could take abuse. They came in large calibers that included not only the very respectable .45-70, but also .45-100, .44-77 Sharps, and .40-90 Ballard. These rounds were extremely accurate at long range while still carrying a tremendous amount of energy downrange. As such, they were among the most popular big game guns of the late 19th and early 20th century and many a prospector, hunter, and homesteader carried them into the wilderness from Colorado to Alaska and felt better for it. 

Let me know if you have questions about this fine rare rifle.

I've had several Combat Veterans call these Mag Locks due to their duty to guard the M16 mags, rifles and other munitions. These are trusted by the US military to keep out even their most trained soldiers! Thats high security! 

These retail for $1800.00 

Internal parts are have residual graphite on them. 

The padlock is in great shape with minor stains, scuffs and marks from use. Please look at photos. There is some VERY MINOR finish missing from the shackle but it wont hender the security and integrity of the padlock in any way. 

This padlock has been designed to resist liquid nitrogen freeze attacks, prying attacks, torch attacks, cutting attacks, explosives attacks and most other forms of physical attack. The Medeco core utilizes special pins that must be lifted and rotated to proper positions in order to allow for the sidebar to retract and free the cylinder; unlocking it. The cylinder has ceramic inserts to help deter drilling attacks. This lock is virtually bump proof. I say virtually, because it is proven that MEDECO can be bumped open, but producing bump keys for medeco locks is a heck of a process that most ordinary people and locksmiths cannot commit to. 

This padlock will meet and surpass your security requirements. 

Make me a reasonable offer. Will trade for other interesting goods. Prefer cash.
